Merge pull request #2 from mozilla/user-js

100 YEARS FOREVER

attempt to override profiles.ini

Firefox's command line switches for starting with a particular profile, specified by path or name, have proven problematic. This patch takes the path of overwriting profiles.ini instead, making the only (and default) profile point at the provided boxen profile.
update the iterm2 package to get around a permissions problem
vendor those new deps and fixup some typos
add OSX and iterm2 includes, move user.js to the new firefox_profile directory

manage the user profile with the profile manager

Aurora no longer describes or honors the `-p` flag for specifying a path to a
profile. This patch uses the profile manager to create a new profile iff one
does not already exist. User.js is dropped into that profile and the process supervisor runs it via the profile manager.
switch to the shorthand argument for indicating which profile to use

switch to user.js over prefs.js

Firefox overwrites prefs.js, making it impossible to update with puppet's notify
pattern. It should never touch user.js, and that file has precedence over
prefs.js, so let's use that instead.

lots still to do:

* install, run, and vendor libs appropriately
* make the exec to start firefox depend on having aurora installed
* customize the profile
* ensure this is a stable way store the profile[1]
* turn on error reporting
* create and install cron.d to restart the browser nightly
* create and install cron.d to run `boxen` nightly
* enable a permanent do not disturb mode [2]
* softwareupdate -l ??

[1] storing the profile in boxen may be a silly idea. if anything in
it changes it will register as a dirty tree and fail any subsequent
updates. If that's the case we will need a dropbox or similar.

[2] DND resets itself periodically (24 hrs?) to prevent a user from
missing security fixes. Let's see if we can get an exec to turn it off
every night when we run boxen.
